main event: On August 3, 1965, five unidentified objects were observed over Cocoa, Florida, changing colors and appearing stationary.
interesting points: The objects changed color from orange to white and were reported to be in a diamond formation., The sighting lasted approximately 4 minutes 15 seconds., Local investigators concluded there was insufficient evidence, attributing the lights to reflections., No photographs or physical evidence were obtained during the investigation., One witness reported a similar sighting earlier in the month.
witness description: Police officers from the Cocoa Police Department
